cast.text:
MICRO TRANSACTION META

1) We're seeing an increasing number of products take advantage of micro-transactions. See: Warpcast Tipping, , , etc.

2) This shift is caused by several converging trends: low gas fees, social identity tied to wallets, and an influx of liquidity (e.g. Warpcast Rewards) that lets users play with "house money". 

3) As txn fees have dropped, new products are emerging that target markets that were previously unavailable due to high fees. See chart below.

4) Warpcast's social graph and product architecture means that users now receive notifications when they are paid, further increasing the virality of products that help users pay each other.

Should we rebrand Warpcast to Farcaster?

We separated Warpcast (the app) from Farcaster (the protocol) a few years ago. 

We've heard from many new users that this is very, very confusing. People hear about Farcaster, search in the app store, can't find anything called Farcaster and then churn.

text:
to avoid confusion, we're building on frames(soon to be mini apps) just like warpcast/farcaster is -- there's no new spec or anything like that. to clarify that first point:
- both clients might handle things like deeplinks differently
- there are a few small things we're working through so there are no limitations for devs to build frames/mini apps that show up in both clients, the main limitation is listed below from the minikit docs

IMO what MiniKit offers is a layer of abstraction that makes it easier to:
- use sdk functions that will work/gracefully fallback both across Warpcast and Coinbase Wallet
- set up certain things like domain account association and notifications that usually take a bit of time
- use all of the other benefits OnchainKit gives you for building a frame

2. Social

Search Improvements — DC & Cast Search significantly improved 

Verifications:
- Goal: make it easy for devs to find users who are valuable to target
   - Current scores are maybe a bit more spam-focused, this helps verify you're a real person in a way that has some "POW" attached
- Supporting Github, Discord & LinkedIn (20k discord, 19k GH, 161k X, 95k phone)
- Explored Worldcoin, need native SDK
- Removed scoring, need to rethink how this works

Topic Based Discovery — seeing if LLMs can be used to categorize casts and pull out unique categories to help discovery(*could* make a personalized Explore page kinda like X)

Experiment: Weekly Kudos —  sending a small tip/gift to your friend, could espc. be powerful for new users who haven't earned crypto before

1. Crypto

Wallet:
   - Focus is still growing usage — over 70,000 funded embedded Warpcast wallets.
    - Separately kicking off an audit on the mobile wallet
    - Exploring the ideas both of a web wallet and Solana support

Frames:
   - More natural discovery, unique frame launches closer to like 35k people now, more volume more transactions
  - Working through changing the name to mini apps
  - Releasing a new Mini Apps docs page very soon(LLM friendly) as well as some developer tooling for scaffolding/testing mini apps

Airdrops:
   - Believe there's a cool opportunity to have airdrops where devs can find users in a more targeted way and lead them towards actions(Bracky is a great example of this) -- and better UX than was previously available
